\section*{Vaccinology}
- Science or methodology of vaccine development
- Scientific research regarding the organism pathogenesis and immune response it confers
- Identification of specific epitopes (antigenic determinants) to use as antigen
- Antigen generation and isolated from cells used to generate it
- Vaccine formulation
- Pre clinical trials in animals
- Clinical trial in human
- Phase 1-<100-safety, immunogenicity, dose response
- Phase 2-safety immunogenicity in several hundreds
- Phase 3-efficacy in thousands
- Phase 4-post marketing surveillance for safety and effectiveness

